        <x-sections.card-image-with-text
            image="/images/business-signs/top5pct-business-signs-joliet-shorewood-crest-hill.jpg"
            alt="Custom storefront business signs in Joliet, Shorewood, and Crest Hill Illinois"
            title="Storefront Business Signs"
        >
            <p class="mb-4">We print and install custom storefront signs for businesses throughout Joliet, Shorewood, Channahon, and all of Will and DuPage County. Your storefront sign is the first thing customers see when they arrive at your location, and it works best when paired with our <a href="/signs/business-signs/window-signs" class="link-notification">window signs</a> that carry your branding from the front wall all the way across your glass. We work with small business owners, retail stores, restaurants, salons, and service companies to create signs that make a lasting first impression, and for brands that want to extend their reach beyond the storefront our <a href="/vehicle-graphics" class="link-notification">vehicle graphics</a> put your logo on every vehicle in your fleet.</p>
            <p class="mb-4">We use premium materials that are rated for years of outdoor exposure in Illinois weather. Our outdoor vinyl signs are UV resistant and can handle everything from summer heat to winter ice without fading or peeling. We prepare every surface before installation and use professional grade adhesion techniques so your sign stays put long after it goes up, and those same standards apply to our <a href="/signs/business-signs/banners" class="link-notification">banner installations</a> and all exterior signage we produce for Will and DuPage County businesses.</p>
            <p><a href="/" class="link-notification">Top 5 Percent</a> is a veteran-owned business located at 121 Springfield Avenue in Joliet, Illinois. We are proud to serve the businesses that make Will and DuPage County and the Chicagoland area a great place to live and work. Call us at <a href="tel:+18153498600" class="link-notification">(815) 349-8600</a> to talk about your storefront signage needs today.</p>
        </x-sections.card-image-with-text>

        <x-sections.card-image-with-text
            image="/images/business-signs/top5pct-outdoor-signs-joliet-shorewood-crest-hill.jpg"
            alt="Custom outdoor business signs in Joliet, Shorewood, and Crest Hill Illinois"
            title="Outdoor Signs Built to Last"
            imagePosition="right"
        >
            <p class="mb-4">We produce outdoor business signs that are designed to withstand Illinois weather year round. From pole signs and monument signs to outdoor banners and post and panel displays, we offer a wide range of outdoor signage solutions, and clients who need mobile advertising alongside their fixed signage can add <a href="/vehicle-graphics" class="link-notification">vehicle graphics</a> to their order. Outdoor signs work around the clock to advertise your business to everyone who drives or walks past your location, and combining them with <a href="/signs/ground-signs/yard-signs" class="link-notification">yard signs</a> at nearby intersections multiplies your local visibility significantly.</p>
            <p class="mb-4">We use aluminum, corrugated plastic, dibond, and PVC board materials depending on the application and the budget. Aluminum is the most durable choice for long term outdoor signage that needs to hold up in extreme weather. Corrugated plastic is the budget friendly choice for temporary outdoor signs and short term promotions, so for a permanent storefront solution see our <a href="/signs/business-signs/window-signs" class="link-notification">window signs</a> printed on long-lasting UV-rated vinyl.</p>
            <p>Our clients in Shorewood, Crest Hill, and Romeoville have trusted us to build outdoor signs that look great from day one and stay looking great for years. We understand the Will and DuPage County climate and we choose materials that are proven to perform in our environment. Give us a call at <a href="tel:+18153498600" class="link-notification">(815) 349-8600</a> and let us help you find the right outdoor sign solution for your business.</p>
        </x-sections.card-image-with-text>

        <x-sections.cta-quadruple-button-banner />

        <x-sections.card-2image-with-text
            image1="/images/business-signs/top5pct-door-signs-joliet-shorewood-crest-hill.jpg"
            alt1="Custom door signs printed and installed in Joliet, Shorewood, and Crest Hill Illinois"
            image2="/images/business-signs/top5pct-window-signs-joliet-new-lenox-shorewood.jpg"
            alt2="Perforated window signs installed for businesses in Joliet, New Lenox, and Shorewood"
            title="Door and Window Signs"
        >
            <p class="mb-4">We transform plain glass doors and windows into powerful advertising tools. Custom window signs let you use the glass on your storefront to communicate your hours, your services, your brand, and your personality without blocking the view from inside. We print on clear vinyl, white vinyl, and perforated window vinyl so you have options depending on how much visibility you want to maintain. Perforated window vinyl looks like a solid graphic from outside while still allowing you to see out from inside your business.</p>
            <p class="mb-4">Door signs are one of our most requested products for businesses in Joliet and New Lenox. A professional door graphic with your business name, hours, phone number, and logo tells customers everything they need to know before they even open the door. We also print frosted vinyl for office doors and glass partitions that creates privacy while maintaining a polished, professional look.</p>
            <p>Our installation team handles the prep and application so the finished product looks perfectly clean and straight every time. Window and door signs from Top 5 Percent are built to last and easy to remove if your branding ever changes. We serve businesses throughout Joliet, Shorewood, New Lenox, Lockport, and all of Will and DuPage County with professional door and window signage at competitive prices.</p>
        </x-sections.card-2image-with-text>

        <x-sections.card-2image-with-text
            image1="/images/business-signs/top5pct-business-signs-joliet-plainfield-romeoville.jpg"
            alt1="Custom business signs for companies in Joliet, Plainfield, and Romeoville Illinois"
            image2="/images/business-signs/top5pct-business-signs-joliet-shorewood-channahon.jpg"
            alt2="Business signs printed and installed in Joliet, Shorewood, and Channahon Illinois"
            title="Signs for Businesses Across Will and DuPage County"
        >
            <p class="mb-4">We serve businesses in every part of Will and DuPage County with custom sign printing and installation services. From small neighborhood shops in Joliet to large commercial operations in Plainfield and Romeoville, we have the experience and the equipment to handle any sign project. Our clients include restaurants, law offices, medical practices, churches, auto repair shops, construction companies, real estate firms, and many other types of businesses. No project is too simple or too complex for our team.</p>
            <p class="mb-4">We also handle sign face replacements for businesses that have existing sign structures but need new printed inserts. Replacing the face of an existing sign is a cost effective way to update your branding without the expense of installing an entirely new structure. We can print to fit nearly any sign cabinet size and we work with standard sign face materials that meet most commercial sign specifications.</p>
            <p>If you are not sure what you need, just give us a call and we will walk you through the options. We are a veteran owned business based in Joliet and we are proud to serve the businesses that make Will and DuPage County a great place to live and work. Our shop is located at 121 Springfield Avenue in Joliet. Call us at <a href="tel:+18153498600" class="link-notification">(815) 349-8600</a> to schedule your consultation today.</p>
        </x-sections.card-2image-with-text>


    <x-sections.product-grid collectionSlug="business-signs" parentSlug="signs" />

            <x-sections.card-detailed-info
                heading="4 Ways Business Signs Help Promote Your Business"
                image1="/images/business-signs/top5pct-article-business-signs-pic1.jpg"
                alt1="Custom business signs that promote local companies in Joliet, Will and DuPage County Illinois"
            >
                <x-slot name="intro">
                    <p class="mb-4">Business signs are one of the most important investments a company can make in its own visibility. A well placed, professionally printed sign works for you around the clock, and it works even better when combined with our <a href="/signs/business-signs/window-signs" class="link-notification">window signs</a> and <a href="/signs/ground-signs/yard-signs" class="link-notification">yard signs</a> for complete coverage at street level. We have been helping businesses across Joliet, Shorewood, Plainfield, and all of Will and DuPage County make a stronger first impression with custom signage since 2017. Here are four ways that a great business sign can directly help your business grow.</p>
                    <h3 class="text-h3 font-bold text-charcoal mb-2">Visibility and Foot Traffic</h3>
                    <p class="mb-4">The most important benefit of a business sign is visibility. When someone drives or walks past your location and sees a bright, clear, and professional sign with your name and what you offer, that information sticks. A significant percentage of new customers find a local business for the first time simply by noticing its sign from the road. In a place like Joliet where Route 30 and Route 59 carry thousands of drivers every day, your sign is competing for attention alongside everything else on the street. A great sign cuts through the noise and gets noticed. We print outdoor business signs in bold colors using UV resistant inks that hold up through Illinois winters and summers alike so your investment looks great year after year.</p>
                </x-slot>
                <x-slot name="mid">
                    <h3 class="text-h3 font-bold text-charcoal mb-2">Brand Identity and Consistency</h3>
                    <p class="mb-4">Your sign is not just a name on a wall. It is a representation of your entire brand, and it works best when your exterior signage coordinates with your <a href="/signs/business-signs/window-signs" class="link-notification">window signs</a> and interior displays for a consistent look at every touchpoint. A sign that looks sharp and professional tells customers that you care about the details, and our <a href="/design-services/logo-design" class="link-notification">design team</a> takes the time to understand your brand before we ever put anything in production so every element coordinates perfectly. We work with business owners throughout the Chicagoland area to design and produce signs that accurately represent their brand and build long term customer loyalty.</p>
                    <h3 class="text-h3 font-bold text-charcoal mb-2">Trust and Credibility</h3>
                    <p class="mb-4">A professional sign builds trust before a customer even walks through your door. When someone in Joliet, Romeoville, or Bolingbrook is comparing two businesses for the first time and one has a clean, well lit sign and the other has a handwritten piece of paper in the window, the choice becomes obvious. Your sign signals to potential customers that your business is legitimate, established, and invested in the quality of the experience it provides. We have helped businesses across Will and DuPage County replace outdated or damaged signs and watched their customer confidence increase almost immediately after the new sign went up, and many of those same clients added <a href="/vehicle-graphics" class="link-notification">vehicle graphics</a> to extend their professional brand image beyond the storefront.</p>
                </x-slot>
                <x-slot name="lower">
                    <h3 class="text-h3 font-bold text-charcoal mb-2">Directional and Wayfinding Signage</h3>
                    <p class="mb-4">Beyond the main storefront sign, directional signs help customers navigate your space confidently and without frustration. Parking signs, entrance signs, suite number markers, restroom signs, and window hour graphics all contribute to a smooth customer experience, and pairing them with <a href="/signs/business-signs/floor-signs" class="link-notification">floor signs</a> guides customers from the moment they step inside. When people can find you easily and know where to park and where to enter, they arrive at your door in a good mood and ready to do business, and our <a href="/signs/business-signs/door-signs" class="link-notification">door signs</a> with hours and contact info give customers all the information they need at eye level before they even open the door.</p>
                    <p class="mb-4">We produce a full range of wayfinding and directional signs for businesses in Joliet, Crest Hill, Lockport, and throughout the broader Chicagoland area. We can assess your location and recommend a complete signage package that covers every touchpoint from the street to the front door. We want every customer who comes to your location to feel welcomed, guided, and impressed by the professionalism of your space.</p>
                </x-slot>
                <x-slot name="footer">
                    <p class="mb-4">We are a veteran owned sign shop located at 121 Springfield Avenue in Joliet, Illinois. We serve businesses of every size across Will and DuPage County and the Chicagoland area, and our full <a href="/signs" class="link-notification">signs shop</a> covers everything from storefront signs to <a href="/signs/ground-signs/yard-signs" class="link-notification">yard signs</a> and vehicle graphics so you never have to go somewhere else to complete your outdoor branding package. Whether you need a single window graphic or a complete exterior signage package, we have the design experience and the production capability to make it happen.</p>
                    <p>Call us at <a href="tel:+18153498600" class="link-notification">(815) 349-8600</a> to schedule a consultation and let us help your business make a stronger statement every single day. We can also pair your signage package with branded <a href="/custom-apparel" class="link-notification">custom apparel</a> for a fully coordinated brand presence at your location and on your team.</p>
                </x-slot>
